## Logcat — Filtered and Actionable

```bash
# Clear buffer first, then stream filtered by package
adb logcat -c && adb logcat --pid=$(adb shell pidof -s <package.name>)

# Filter by tag (e.g., your app tag)
adb logcat -s MyAppTag:D

# Capture crash — show only errors and above
adb logcat *:E

# Save logcat to file with timestamps
adb logcat -v threadtime > logcat_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).txt

# Detect ANR signals
adb logcat | grep -i "ANR\|Choreographer\|skipped.*frames"

# Monitor a specific class
adb logcat | grep "UserRepository"
```

**Logcat levels**: V (verbose) D (debug) I (info) W (warn) E (error) F (fatal)

